import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='Miles_per_Gallon', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['Miles_per_Gallon'].mean():.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median():.2f}")
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Miles_per_Gallon?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='Year', y='Miles_per_Gallon', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['Miles_per_Gallon'].median(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Median')
    chart.legend()
    plt.title('What is the trend of Miles_per_Gallon over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
